entry.title: Coastal Flood Advisory issued December 18 at 1:44PM AKST until December 19 at 11:00AM AKST by NWS Anchorage AK
entry.summary:
* WHAT...Water levels as high as 3 to 4 feet above normal highest tide are expected, with locally higher water levels possible.
* WHERE...Kwigillingok.
* WHEN...Water levels will rise overnight tonight and remain elevated through late Thursday morning. The highest water levels will coincide with high tide.
* IMPACTS...Water levels and impacts will be similar to what was observed last night, with minor flooding of lakes and low lying areas.
* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Winds last night were out of the southeast at around 15 to 30 mph. Winds tonight will be a bit weaker and will take on a more easterly direction. While this wind direction is not typically favorable for coastal flooding, the ground is saturated due to last night's flooding and rising water levels will coincide with the high tide, expectedly strong due to the full moon. Additionally, due to the lack of abundant shorefast ice, this will allow for higher water levels. Other communities along the Kuskokwim Delta coast may see elevated water levels in the early morning hours similarly to last night.
